WEBVTT

00:01.700 --> 00:03.700
[birds calling]

00:07.420 --> 00:09.420
[music playing on radio]

00:19.580 --> 00:21.780
[music continues]

00:38.780 --> 00:39.780
[sighs]

01:02.460 --> 01:04.459
[engine and music turn off]

01:27.260 --> 01:29.220
♪ ♪

01:40.980 --> 01:41.980
[faint gunshot]

01:42.060 --> 01:43.060
[gasps]

01:54.860 --> 01:57.860
[doors creaks loudly]

01:59.260 --> 02:00.500
Hello?

02:18.700 --> 02:22.460
[banging]

02:30.740 --> 02:33.660
Hi.

02:33.740 --> 02:36.500
I'm looking for the...

02:36.580 --> 02:39.060
[engine revving loudly]

02:47.060 --> 02:55.980
♪ Tram wires
cross northern skies ♪

02:56.060 --> 03:01.980
♪ Cut my blue heart in two ♪

03:02.060 --> 03:09.420
♪ My knuckles bleed
down the tattered street ♪

03:09.460 --> 03:16.900
♪ On a door that shouldn't be
in front of me ♪

03:16.980 --> 03:18.980
[panting]

03:41.540 --> 03:45.020
[faint siren blaring]

03:51.140 --> 03:52.540
[groans]

04:04.900 --> 04:05.900
[sighs]

04:12.420 --> 04:14.860
[computer ringing]

04:21.500 --> 04:25.100
[ringing continues]

04:30.340 --> 04:31.500
<i>Hi, Dad.</i>

04:31.580 --> 04:33.460
Oh, hi, hi, hi.

04:33.500 --> 04:35.540
<i>You made it!</i>

04:35.620 --> 04:36.740
<i>How is it?</i>

04:36.820 --> 04:38.420
It's, uh...

04:38.460 --> 04:39.420
It's sunny.

04:39.460 --> 04:40.900
Be good if you were here.

04:40.980 --> 04:42.300
How's Klara?

04:42.380 --> 04:43.980
<i>She's good-- she's at nursery.</i>

04:44.060 --> 04:45.260
<i>When's your speech?</i>

04:45.340 --> 04:48.260
My speech is, uh...

04:48.340 --> 04:49.780
not till Saturday.

04:49.860 --> 04:51.060
<i>Wear your nice suit.</i>

04:51.140 --> 04:53.340
Yes, and I have shaved.

04:53.420 --> 04:55.180
<i>You nervous?</i>

04:55.260 --> 04:57.860
Um... no.

04:57.940 --> 05:00.660
I'm just not quite sure
how to pitch it.

05:00.700 --> 05:02.460
<i>Just say what you feel.</i>

05:02.500 --> 05:05.020
I don't want to waste
anybody's time, is all.

05:05.060 --> 05:07.140
<i>You've got good instincts, Dad.</i>

05:07.220 --> 05:08.540
<i>Just follow them.</i>

05:08.620 --> 05:09.820
Sure, I will.

05:09.860 --> 05:11.460
I just, uh...

05:11.500 --> 05:13.540
You know, I want it to...

05:13.620 --> 05:15.140
I've come all this way.

05:15.220 --> 05:16.820
I just want it to...

05:17.860 --> 05:18.780
mean something.

05:18.860 --> 05:19.780
[call ends abruptly]

05:19.860 --> 05:20.780
Hello?

05:20.860 --> 05:21.860
Hello?

05:22.860 --> 05:23.860
Hello?

05:52.820 --> 05:55.340
[elevator beeping]

06:00.740 --> 06:02.020
After you.

06:06.220 --> 06:07.740
MAN [yelling]:
What are you doing here?!

06:07.820 --> 06:09.180
MAN:
Mr. Hedeman, please...

06:09.260 --> 06:11.300
HEDEMAN:
Eh? Why are you
wasting time here?!

06:11.380 --> 06:12.860
MAN:
This is not the time
or the place.

06:12.940 --> 06:14.500
HEDEMAN:
Where's my wife?

06:14.580 --> 06:16.020
Mr. Hedeman, please,
we are at a conference.

06:16.060 --> 06:17.500
Can we deal
with this later?

06:17.580 --> 06:18.780
You've got all these
extra staff now, haven't you?

06:18.860 --> 06:20.260
MAN:
Please, we are
investigating the case.

06:20.340 --> 06:21.540
We're doing
the best we can.

06:21.620 --> 06:22.780
HEDEMAN:
Well then, find her!

06:22.860 --> 06:24.020
She's out there
somewhere!

06:24.060 --> 06:25.740
Why aren't you
doing anything?!

06:27.020 --> 06:28.020
Get off me!

06:28.300 --> 06:29.580
[trailing off]:
Take your hands off me!

06:29.660 --> 06:31.500
I said get off me!

06:44.460 --> 06:45.820
Hi.

06:45.860 --> 06:47.980
Good morning,
ladies and gentlemen.

06:48.060 --> 06:51.260
So today, day two,

06:51.300 --> 06:54.540
we have another gentleman
to speak to you--

06:54.620 --> 06:59.180
something of a legendary person
here in the Western Cape.

06:59.260 --> 07:04.140
A one-time communist,
firebrand, freedom fighter,

07:04.220 --> 07:06.460
joining us today
in his capacity

07:06.500 --> 07:08.860
as chair of the Tourism
Committee,

07:08.940 --> 07:11.260
please welcome Mr. Max Khulu.

07:11.300 --> 07:14.180
[applause]

07:14.260 --> 07:15.500
Thank you.

07:19.020 --> 07:20.860
Thank you.

07:20.940 --> 07:23.460
Please, please.

07:23.540 --> 07:24.780
Thank you.

07:24.860 --> 07:26.060
Thank you, Colonel.

07:26.140 --> 07:27.580
You're welcome.

07:27.660 --> 07:30.020
So, looking out
of the shining windows

07:30.060 --> 07:31.820
of this brand new hotel,

07:31.860 --> 07:34.300
one of many hundreds,

07:34.380 --> 07:38.860
it is not hard to see
how tourism provides

07:38.900 --> 07:42.580
one in every 12 jobs
in South Africa today.

07:42.660 --> 07:45.580
You good-looking foreigners
want to come here

07:45.660 --> 07:47.980
and spend your
good-looking money.

07:48.060 --> 07:49.420
[laughter]

07:49.460 --> 07:51.660
I think it's
a brilliant idea.

07:51.740 --> 07:56.220
But we must be
considerate hosts.

07:56.260 --> 07:58.580
We must take care
of our guests.

07:58.660 --> 08:01.660
If our guests do not feel
that they will be safe,

08:01.700 --> 08:02.980
they will not come.

08:03.060 --> 08:04.500
It is the duty
of our police force

08:04.580 --> 08:08.700
to ensure that never happens.

08:08.780 --> 08:11.460
[applause]

08:13.340 --> 08:16.700
[chattering]

08:36.220 --> 08:37.580
Hi.

08:37.659 --> 08:39.340
Julian Van Heerden.

08:39.419 --> 08:41.179
Kurt Wallander.

08:41.260 --> 08:43.659
I have a gentleman,
a Swedish gentleman,

08:43.740 --> 08:45.180
living out at Sir Lowry's Pass.

08:45.260 --> 08:47.060
Axel Hedeman.

08:47.140 --> 08:48.580
His wife's been missing
for ten days.

08:48.660 --> 08:50.100
Yeah, I've read about it.

08:50.180 --> 08:53.580
To be blunt, he's causing us
a lot of difficulty.

08:53.660 --> 08:55.940
And he's refusing to cooperate,
he's talking to the press...

08:56.020 --> 08:57.660
I think you saw
he brought them here.

08:57.700 --> 09:01.460
It's never easy just waiting
for news, as you know.

09:01.500 --> 09:03.940
Look, uh...

09:05.980 --> 09:09.580
I was wondering
if you could maybe talk to him.

09:09.660 --> 09:11.140
You know,
countryman to countryman.

09:11.220 --> 09:13.140
I think he needs
some reassurance

09:13.220 --> 09:14.700
that we're not just
corrupt amateurs.

09:14.780 --> 09:17.460
Well, I'm sure ultimately
he understands that...

09:17.540 --> 09:20.380
I would really, really
appreciate this.

09:20.460 --> 09:21.940
I'd be grateful.

09:24.740 --> 09:26.300
Could I see
the case notes?

09:26.380 --> 09:27.980
Yeah, of course.

09:28.060 --> 09:29.660
I'll even get someone
to drive you out there.

09:29.700 --> 09:30.660
My sergeant can meet you...

09:30.700 --> 09:31.980
The case notes will do.

09:32.060 --> 09:33.660
If you give me the address,
I'll drive myself.

09:36.540 --> 09:39.940
You do understand that
his wife is missing,

09:40.020 --> 09:43.060
so we're not closing down
certain avenues.

09:43.140 --> 09:44.580
Understood.

09:47.660 --> 09:49.340
Thank you.

09:49.420 --> 09:51.380
Thank you very much.

10:04.780 --> 10:06.820
♪ ♪

10:35.860 --> 10:37.500
[kids shouting]

10:56.860 --> 10:58.260
Detective Inspector Wallander?

10:58.300 --> 10:59.260
Sergeant Matembu?

10:59.300 --> 11:00.260
Mthembu.

11:00.300 --> 11:01.580
Mthembu, sorry.

11:01.660 --> 11:03.060
We appreciate this.

11:05.340 --> 11:07.020
There was no mention
in the file

11:07.060 --> 11:08.900
of a background check
on Hedeman.

11:08.980 --> 11:10.860
We did put in a request.

11:10.900 --> 11:14.580
We're still waiting to hear back
from the Swedish police.

11:17.780 --> 11:19.180
The one place in the country
you know she isn't,

11:19.260 --> 11:21.420
and here you are.

11:21.460 --> 11:23.500
This is Detective
Kurt Wallander.

11:23.580 --> 11:26.580
I'm from Sweden--
Ystad Police.

11:26.660 --> 11:28.700
Good.

11:28.780 --> 11:30.700
It's about time.

11:30.780 --> 11:32.940
Maybe you can do something about
finding my wife.

11:33.020 --> 11:34.300
Come on, guys,
don't just leave them there.

11:34.380 --> 11:35.580
Take them inside and put them
on the counter, yeah?

11:35.660 --> 11:38.260
Otherwise, they'll be stinking
next time we use them.

11:43.420 --> 11:45.340
Most of them are
ex-offenders.

11:45.420 --> 11:47.300
What do you do
for them, sir?

11:47.380 --> 11:49.700
Gym, soccer...

11:49.780 --> 11:51.460
Some kind of male
role model.

11:51.500 --> 11:52.940
That's my side.

11:53.020 --> 11:54.660
And your wife,
what did, uh...

11:54.700 --> 11:56.060
Inga.

11:56.100 --> 11:57.980
She's a teacher.

12:00.380 --> 12:01.980
What's that nasty cut
you have there?

12:02.060 --> 12:04.460
I teach them boxing.

12:04.540 --> 12:06.940
Don't look at me like that.

12:07.020 --> 12:08.500
That's the way they look at me
when they're not helping--

12:08.580 --> 12:09.900
not looking.

12:09.980 --> 12:11.420
Why aren't they looking?

12:11.460 --> 12:12.900
How can there be
nothing after...

12:12.980 --> 12:14.420
This type of inquiry is
very difficult to rush.

12:14.460 --> 12:15.580
After 72 hours,

12:15.660 --> 12:17.060
you're not looking
for a person anymore.

12:17.100 --> 12:19.180
You're looking
for a corpse, right?

12:19.260 --> 12:20.740
It's been more than
247 hours now.

12:20.820 --> 12:22.260
MTHEMBU:
Mr. Hedeman...

12:22.300 --> 12:23.620
WALLANDER:
I've seen the case notes,

12:23.660 --> 12:24.900
and Sergeant Mthembu
and her colleagues

12:24.980 --> 12:26.580
are doing
everything they can.

12:26.660 --> 12:28.260
I know it's frustrating,

12:28.300 --> 12:31.980
but if you talk to the press
and not to the police,

12:32.060 --> 12:35.580
it's getting in the way
of the investigation.

12:35.660 --> 12:37.580
You may be decreasing
the chances of them

12:37.660 --> 12:38.660
finding your wife.

12:42.740 --> 12:44.460
Do you think
she could still be alive?

12:44.500 --> 12:48.220
Yes, of course she could.

12:50.700 --> 12:51.820
Right.

12:54.380 --> 12:58.060
Right, well, thank you.

12:59.820 --> 13:01.100
Come on, guys, off you go.

13:01.180 --> 13:02.420
I'll see you at the center.

13:09.060 --> 13:10.660
We'll be in touch, sir.

13:27.180 --> 13:29.300
That was helpful, thanks.

13:29.380 --> 13:30.500
Oh, you're welcome.

13:30.580 --> 13:31.740
Yeah, um...

13:31.820 --> 13:33.460
Enjoy the rest
of your conference.

13:33.540 --> 13:35.180
Oh, that's right.

13:35.260 --> 13:36.420
Thanks.

13:36.460 --> 13:37.780
Oh, great.

13:37.860 --> 13:39.060
Nice to meet you.

13:39.100 --> 13:40.100
You too.

13:46.100 --> 13:48.020
[engine revving]

14:20.660 --> 14:22.420
Sorry, uh...

14:22.460 --> 14:24.060
Where Inga was going
that day,

14:24.140 --> 14:25.540
is that somewhere
she'd been before?

14:25.620 --> 14:26.980
No.

14:27.060 --> 14:29.060
It was
an outreach center.

14:29.140 --> 14:30.460
She went to pick up
some textbooks

14:30.500 --> 14:32.060
they weren't using anymore.

14:32.140 --> 14:33.820
She never got there.

14:33.860 --> 14:35.860
Do you have
an address?

14:37.220 --> 14:38.740
I've got the directions
somewhere.

14:38.820 --> 14:40.460
Right, thanks.

15:14.900 --> 15:16.260
[door creaking]

15:20.460 --> 15:22.820
This is the place.

15:22.860 --> 15:25.180
Thanks.

15:25.260 --> 15:29.900
This is a faith-based
program, yes?

15:29.980 --> 15:33.900
Everything here is faith-based,
one way or another.

15:33.980 --> 15:35.260
You need it.

15:37.860 --> 15:40.540
I thought being here
might challenge my faith.

15:40.620 --> 15:41.780
Has it?

15:41.860 --> 15:43.580
It has.

15:43.660 --> 15:45.700
But not in the way
I was expecting.

15:49.300 --> 15:50.980
Thank you for this.

15:54.460 --> 15:57.580
I need you to chase up
an information request

15:57.660 --> 15:59.220
for the local police here.

15:59.260 --> 16:00.420
WOMAN: <i>
Do you have a name?</i>

16:00.460 --> 16:02.380
Yeah, the name is Axel Hedeman.

16:02.460 --> 16:04.460
He's from Degeberga.

16:04.500 --> 16:05.940
<i>Okay, leave it with me,
I'll call you back.</i>

16:06.020 --> 16:08.620
Yeah, as soon as possible.

16:08.660 --> 16:09.660
Bye.

16:22.500 --> 16:24.260
♪ ♪

17:11.619 --> 17:13.540
♪ ♪

17:30.500 --> 17:32.380
[engine turns off]

17:38.660 --> 17:40.060
Hello?

17:41.460 --> 17:42.860
Hello?

18:09.780 --> 18:11.420
Hello?

18:11.460 --> 18:13.900
[door creaking]

18:13.980 --> 18:15.260
Hello?

18:38.260 --> 18:42.060
[flies buzzing]

19:12.540 --> 19:14.980
[dialing number]

19:37.060 --> 19:40.540
[continues dialing]

19:40.620 --> 19:43.460
<i>[phone ringing]</i>

19:43.500 --> 19:44.620
<i>Hello?</i>

19:44.660 --> 19:46.380
Hi Grace, it's Kurt.

19:54.060 --> 19:56.180
[metal creaking in wind]

20:05.620 --> 20:07.940
[faint chatter]

20:20.820 --> 20:22.220
How'd you find
this place?

20:22.260 --> 20:24.020
I got lost.

20:24.060 --> 20:26.060
The map's wrong.

20:28.580 --> 20:31.100
Maybe Inga did
the same thing.

20:37.420 --> 20:39.740
Hedeman never
gave us this.

20:39.820 --> 20:42.900
He gave us an address,
that's all.

20:46.540 --> 20:48.180
Hedeman could have
hired somebody

20:48.260 --> 20:49.740
to do his dirty work.

20:55.980 --> 20:57.780
She could have been followed.

20:59.700 --> 21:01.100
Where better?

21:35.660 --> 21:38.580
Cutting their fingers off,

21:38.660 --> 21:42.860
does that mean anything
in tribal, or...?

21:42.900 --> 21:43.900
Tribal?

21:46.700 --> 21:49.260
It means something to the man
who has his fingers cut off.

22:00.340 --> 22:01.660
Good shot.

22:11.700 --> 22:14.100
Everyone out here has a gun.

22:18.500 --> 22:20.260
Let's talk to Hedeman.

22:37.180 --> 22:39.100
♪ ♪

22:50.420 --> 22:53.900
[phone ringing]

22:53.980 --> 22:55.700
Yeah, hello?

22:55.780 --> 22:57.700
WOMAN: <i>
Hi Kurt, I have the information
you wanted on Axel Hedeman.</i>

22:57.780 --> 22:59.380
<i>He has a previous conviction--
aggravated assault.</i>

22:59.460 --> 23:02.540
Right, okay, hold on a sec,
let me just...

23:07.220 --> 23:08.220
Yeah.

23:10.380 --> 23:11.380
Yep.

23:12.540 --> 23:13.860
Anything since?

23:16.860 --> 23:18.140
Okay, thanks.

23:18.220 --> 23:19.580
Okay, bye.

23:20.300 --> 23:22.260
He's not here.

23:22.340 --> 23:25.260
So, Hedeman has
a criminal record in Sweden.

23:25.300 --> 23:27.220
Aggravated assault.

23:27.260 --> 23:30.100
Ten-month
suspended sentence.

23:30.180 --> 23:33.300
He broke his girlfriend's arm
when he was drunk.

23:33.380 --> 23:34.780
It was 2001.

23:37.500 --> 23:39.340
It wasn't his wife?

23:39.420 --> 23:41.420
Nothing reported since.

23:45.340 --> 23:47.820
He did say he was going
to the community center.

23:47.860 --> 23:49.180
Shall we?

23:53.300 --> 24:00.420
MAN:
The ANC has forgotten
its principles,

24:00.460 --> 24:03.420
and we have forgotten
our promise:

24:03.460 --> 24:06.620
the basic
and fundamental promise

24:06.660 --> 24:08.460
that the wealth
of this country...

24:08.500 --> 24:10.820
GRACE:
Municipal elections.

24:10.860 --> 24:13.060
His name's Bernie Meyiwa.

24:13.100 --> 24:15.060
ANC.

24:15.100 --> 24:17.060
Max Khulu's protégé.

24:17.100 --> 24:18.380
[cheering]

24:18.460 --> 24:22.380
The ANC has been dominated...

24:22.460 --> 24:24.220
Six months ago,
a white student

24:24.260 --> 24:26.260
tried his luck
with a 9-millimeter.

24:26.340 --> 24:28.820
...men who have abandoned
our principles.

24:28.860 --> 24:30.580
Men who think that

24:30.660 --> 24:36.700
they can come here
and lie to you and fool you

24:36.780 --> 24:41.060
with lazy, costly words
and rhetoric.

24:41.140 --> 24:45.620
Instead of building
luxury houses, luxury hotels

24:45.660 --> 24:48.860
where rich foreigners
can line their pockets

24:48.900 --> 24:51.460
with your money

24:51.540 --> 24:55.340
right next door
to your community,

24:55.420 --> 25:00.340
we should be building you
affordable homes!

25:00.420 --> 25:04.220
We should make sure that
you can feel our wealth!

25:04.260 --> 25:06.940
You can feel
the improvements!

25:07.020 --> 25:10.620
You can feel that there is
someone better for you,

25:10.660 --> 25:12.260
for all of us, to go!

25:12.340 --> 25:14.540
So, is he gonna get in?

25:14.620 --> 25:16.660
Well, I'm gonna vote for him.

25:18.220 --> 25:20.780
[chanting]

25:20.860 --> 25:23.180
HEDEMAN:
Come on, keep your guard up!

25:25.660 --> 25:27.020
See? That's what's happens.

25:27.060 --> 25:28.820
Keep your elbows in,
elbows in!

25:31.980 --> 25:33.460
That's it,
come on!

25:33.540 --> 25:35.020
Mr. Hedeman.

25:45.780 --> 25:48.460
Do you recognize
this, sir?

25:51.460 --> 25:52.660
Yes, I recognize it.

25:52.700 --> 25:53.660
Where did you find it?

25:53.700 --> 25:55.300
She never takes this off.

25:55.380 --> 25:57.660
It was found
at an old stock farm

25:57.700 --> 25:59.260
off the road your wife
would have taken.

25:59.340 --> 26:01.980
According to a map you gave
the Detective Inspector here.

26:02.060 --> 26:03.420
But why would she...?

26:03.460 --> 26:04.860
Did you find the car?

26:04.900 --> 26:06.220
There was a wrong turn
on the map,

26:06.260 --> 26:08.460
so Inga might have
got lost.

26:08.500 --> 26:10.260
Why didn't you give the map
to us, sir,

26:10.340 --> 26:12.340
when you reported
your wife missing?

26:12.420 --> 26:13.740
It would have helped.

26:16.940 --> 26:19.180
No, I...

26:19.260 --> 26:20.700
I gave you the address.

26:20.780 --> 26:22.860
I didn't think...

26:22.900 --> 26:24.660
You have a history.

26:24.740 --> 26:26.060
We all have a history.

26:26.140 --> 26:27.940
Some of us overcome it.

26:31.900 --> 26:35.860
[phone ringing]

26:35.900 --> 26:36.860
Grace.

26:36.900 --> 26:38.100
Excuse me.

26:38.180 --> 26:39.020
Hi.

26:39.060 --> 26:40.660
No other sign of her?

26:40.740 --> 26:42.660
No, nothing.

26:48.460 --> 26:50.060
She, um...

26:53.060 --> 26:56.900
That was the first time
she drove on her own here.

26:58.420 --> 27:00.980
She was afraid of being
on her own.

27:01.060 --> 27:02.660
Being lost.

27:04.620 --> 27:06.340
Excuse me, sorry.

27:11.180 --> 27:13.060
I have a match
on the prints.

27:13.100 --> 27:14.980
Belongs to a low-level
gang member.

27:15.060 --> 27:17.140
A tsotsi.

27:17.220 --> 27:19.740
Mr. Hedeman,
we'll find her.

27:46.460 --> 27:47.980
GRACE:
You have something for me?

27:48.060 --> 27:49.460
MAN:
Yeah.

27:49.500 --> 27:51.660
The boy's name is
Victor Mabasha.

27:51.740 --> 27:53.020
Member of the 26s.

27:53.060 --> 27:54.460
It's a prison gang.

27:54.500 --> 27:56.460
Interviewed in 2012
in Pollsmoor

27:56.500 --> 27:57.900
about the murder
of a prison guard--

27:57.980 --> 27:59.940
his initiation
into the 26s.

28:00.020 --> 28:01.340
Not charged--
lack of evidence.

28:01.420 --> 28:02.340
What else?

28:02.420 --> 28:03.340
He's nothing big.

28:03.420 --> 28:04.340
A foot soldier.

28:04.420 --> 28:05.700
He's just a kid,
isn't he?

28:05.780 --> 28:07.060
They're all just kids.

28:07.100 --> 28:09.540
I mean, they don't live
long enough to grow up.

28:09.620 --> 28:11.060
He hangs out at a shebeen.

28:11.140 --> 28:13.460
Bomba's,
near Khayelitsha station.

28:13.540 --> 28:14.980
Is this reliable?

28:15.060 --> 28:17.380
As reliable as any
of the other leads.

28:17.460 --> 28:20.460
Right, so we take
a detachment out there,

28:20.500 --> 28:22.060
you see if there's
any connection

28:22.100 --> 28:23.820
between Mabasha
and the Hedemans,

28:23.860 --> 28:25.660
specifically see if he was
one of their projects.

28:25.740 --> 28:27.420
Do you want to come with me
to Bomba's?

28:27.460 --> 28:28.860
Some real sightseeing.

28:28.940 --> 28:30.620
It's fine, Sergeant.

28:30.660 --> 28:33.100
Thanks for your help.

28:33.180 --> 28:35.060
We'll need a statement
concerning the stock farm.

28:35.100 --> 28:37.220
I could send someone over
to the hotel.

28:37.260 --> 28:38.940
WALLANDER:
Sure, sure.

28:39.020 --> 28:40.940
Enjoy the rest
of the conference.

28:41.020 --> 28:41.820
All right, thanks.

28:41.860 --> 28:42.620
Sergeant.

28:42.660 --> 28:43.620
Yes.

28:43.660 --> 28:44.660
Thanks, Kurt.

29:03.980 --> 29:05.900
♪ ♪

29:23.860 --> 29:25.620
[sighs]

29:55.380 --> 29:56.460
♪ ♪

30:06.260 --> 30:08.860
[dialing number]

30:08.940 --> 30:12.380
<i>[phone ringing]</i>

30:12.460 --> 30:15.100
OPERATOR: <i>
The subscriber you have dialed
is not available at present.</i>

30:20.900 --> 30:22.020
Excuse me.

30:22.060 --> 30:23.180
Good day, sir.

30:23.260 --> 30:26.660
Do you know where
Khayelitsha station is?

30:35.100 --> 30:36.820
♪ ♪

30:53.060 --> 30:54.580
[kids shouting]

31:13.380 --> 31:15.860
[men talking loudly]

31:32.860 --> 31:35.060
[reggae music playing]

31:55.060 --> 31:57.740
Hi, um... Bomba's?

31:57.820 --> 31:59.460
[laughing]

31:59.500 --> 32:00.460
Bomba's?

32:00.500 --> 32:01.460
Excuse me.

32:01.500 --> 32:02.460
Yeah?

32:02.500 --> 32:03.260
Left, up there.

32:03.300 --> 32:05.580
Up there, it's left.

32:05.660 --> 32:07.420
Right, thank you.

32:07.460 --> 32:09.140
Easy on the Umqombothi.

32:09.220 --> 32:10.220
Okay.

32:17.660 --> 32:18.660
[man shouting]

32:31.220 --> 32:33.140
[dance music playing]

32:33.220 --> 32:36.140
[people talking loudly]

32:49.700 --> 32:50.700
Hello.

32:53.300 --> 32:55.580
Do you have
a sparkling water?

32:55.660 --> 32:57.620
Yes, yes.

33:07.220 --> 33:08.220
Thanks.

33:55.340 --> 33:58.980
<i>[phone ringing]</i>

33:59.060 --> 33:59.660
Police?

33:59.700 --> 34:01.860
I... I'm not.

34:01.940 --> 34:03.060
Who are you?

34:03.140 --> 34:04.380
I'm just... Kurt.

34:04.460 --> 34:05.460
Go sit there.

34:05.540 --> 34:07.180
Okay.

34:07.260 --> 34:08.980
Sit.

34:12.260 --> 34:13.540
I'm not South African.

34:13.620 --> 34:14.540
No!

34:14.620 --> 34:16.060
I'm not South African.

34:16.139 --> 34:17.860
I'll just show you my ID.

34:24.980 --> 34:26.860
I just want to talk.

34:26.900 --> 34:28.940
Just talk, that's all.

34:29.020 --> 34:30.420
Take the money,
we can talk.

34:34.620 --> 34:36.580
Do you recognize her?

34:43.060 --> 34:43.980
I just...

34:44.060 --> 34:45.219
Listen, listen

34:45.260 --> 34:47.860
What happened out there
at the stock farm?

34:47.940 --> 34:51.860
How did that happen?

34:51.900 --> 34:54.620
You must be in real pain.

34:54.659 --> 34:57.780
I just want to find out
what happened to her.

34:57.860 --> 35:00.180
That's all.

35:00.260 --> 35:01.820
Where do you come from?

35:01.860 --> 35:05.660
I'm from Sweden.

35:05.700 --> 35:07.260
And so does she.

35:07.340 --> 35:09.540
I come from a country
called Sweden,

35:09.620 --> 35:11.340
we both come from Sweden.

35:13.060 --> 35:14.380
It's all right.

35:18.700 --> 35:19.660
Look out!

35:25.140 --> 35:26.700
[gunshots]

35:36.660 --> 35:38.380
[engine revving]

36:05.780 --> 36:07.500
♪ ♪

36:25.260 --> 36:27.140
[dogs barking]

36:32.860 --> 36:34.940
[laughing]

36:58.460 --> 37:03.180
OFFICER:
...lines of enquiry, but the
location was linked to our lead.

37:03.260 --> 37:06.540
REPORTER:
...there were several gunshots,
is that correct?

37:06.620 --> 37:07.980
OFFICER:
We're still gathering evidence.

37:08.060 --> 37:09.660
Once we have all the
information,

37:09.700 --> 37:11.340
I'll be holding
a press conference.

37:11.420 --> 37:12.820
REPORTER:
Do you believe that Mrs. Hedeman
could still be alive?

37:12.860 --> 37:13.820
OFFICER:
Absolutely.

37:13.860 --> 37:15.180
Thanks.

37:15.260 --> 37:17.220
OFFICER:
We remain positive
that we will find her.

37:17.260 --> 37:18.380
I can assure you

37:18.460 --> 37:20.660
we have our best team
out there looking for her.

37:20.740 --> 37:22.060
What are you
doing here, Kurt?

37:23.180 --> 37:25.220
I just...

37:25.260 --> 37:27.620
I thought that you'd be...

37:27.660 --> 37:30.260
I'm sorry.

37:30.340 --> 37:32.900
I tried to call.

37:32.980 --> 37:34.820
Yeah?

37:34.860 --> 37:38.780
So you should have
waited for a reply.

37:38.860 --> 37:41.180
We have people.

37:41.260 --> 37:43.260
You know about
surveillance?

37:45.060 --> 37:46.300
Khulu wants to see you.

37:46.380 --> 37:47.460
Both of you.

37:48.940 --> 37:51.100
Get Max off my back,
for God's sake.

37:52.140 --> 37:53.140
Sir.

37:56.660 --> 37:58.460
REPORTER: <i>
There have been reports
of a shootout in Khayelitsha</i>

37:58.500 --> 38:00.340
<i>involving a Swedish
national this afternoon.</i>

38:00.420 --> 38:02.660
<i>Reports suggest that
the shootout was linked</i>

38:02.700 --> 38:04.100
<i>to the recent disappearance...</i>

38:09.820 --> 38:11.660
[beeping]

38:33.580 --> 38:35.620
Sir, was I wrong
in assuming that

38:35.660 --> 38:40.780
the purpose of your involvement
was to limit bad news stories?

38:40.860 --> 38:42.580
Max, try to be polite.

38:42.660 --> 38:44.060
They're guests.

38:44.140 --> 38:45.740
Behave yourself.

38:45.820 --> 38:47.300
Behave?

38:47.380 --> 38:51.060
These Swedes
should behave themselves!

38:51.140 --> 38:54.060
Max has a habit
of talking to people

38:54.100 --> 38:56.300
like he's addressing
a public meeting.

38:56.380 --> 38:58.620
Take your pills, dear.

38:58.660 --> 38:59.620
[laughs]

38:59.660 --> 39:00.620
Pleasure meeting you.

39:00.660 --> 39:02.820
BOTH:
Thank you.

39:02.860 --> 39:05.020
So, how did
our Swedish friend

39:05.060 --> 39:08.020
know to search for this boy
in the Flats?

39:08.060 --> 39:10.060
I was just looking
for my own...

39:10.140 --> 39:11.980
Did you see the shooter?

39:12.060 --> 39:13.260
He was wearing...

39:13.300 --> 39:14.460
I can't... no.

39:14.500 --> 39:16.060
I know that he was white.

39:16.140 --> 39:17.460
And a registration number?

39:17.500 --> 39:19.260
No, I didn't get it.

39:25.700 --> 39:27.660
Do you think
it was her husband?

39:27.700 --> 39:31.340
Axel Hedeman does have
a history of violence.

39:31.420 --> 39:34.980
So, he hired this boy Mabasha
to kill his wife for him?

39:35.060 --> 39:36.460
It's a possibility.

39:42.900 --> 39:44.260
These are cut
from the plants

39:44.300 --> 39:46.540
I kept in the garden
at Pollsmoor prison.

39:46.620 --> 39:50.260
This tsotsi has been
in Pollsmoor.

39:50.340 --> 39:52.020
Yeah.

39:52.060 --> 39:55.380
How much would he get
for a life?

39:55.460 --> 39:57.940
GRACE:
Next to nothing.

39:58.020 --> 40:00.260
MAX:
Ten thousand rand?

40:04.260 --> 40:08.660
So that's what a man
sells his freedom for.

40:08.740 --> 40:11.660
I wish we'd known the price
30 years ago.

40:11.740 --> 40:13.940
[peacocks calling]

40:17.300 --> 40:19.260
Do you have
anything more?

40:19.340 --> 40:21.020
No.

40:21.060 --> 40:25.260
I appreciate you taking the time
to come here, Sergeant.

40:25.340 --> 40:27.180
Keep us informed.

40:27.260 --> 40:30.860
I think we'd all like to put it
to bed as soon as possible.

40:30.940 --> 40:33.860
As much as it's been a pleasure,
Mr. Wallander,

40:33.940 --> 40:37.820
I don't expect we'll be
seeing each other again.

40:43.300 --> 40:46.060
[peacocks calling]

40:51.620 --> 40:53.540
♪ ♪

41:05.060 --> 41:06.060
[sighs]

41:12.860 --> 41:14.820
Sorry, I'm...

41:14.860 --> 41:16.020
Wallander, from...

41:16.060 --> 41:17.420
I've lost my room keys.

41:17.460 --> 41:18.780
107-- sorry.

41:18.860 --> 41:20.860
Okay, no problem.

41:22.940 --> 41:24.260
All right, sorry about that.

41:24.340 --> 41:25.340
Thanks.

41:27.300 --> 41:29.900
[men laughing]

42:01.700 --> 42:02.860
[gun clicks]

42:17.460 --> 42:19.060
Okay, put the gun down.

42:19.100 --> 42:21.100
I'll talk to you
if you put the gun down.

42:21.180 --> 42:22.980
What are you doing?

42:23.060 --> 42:24.060
Let's go.

42:25.860 --> 42:27.140
Let's go.

42:51.460 --> 42:53.460
[men laughing]

43:10.700 --> 43:12.220
Turn right.

43:23.980 --> 43:25.900
Victor, where am I driving?

43:25.980 --> 43:27.420
You don't need to know.

43:27.460 --> 43:28.900
Just drive.

44:05.980 --> 44:06.980
Drive on.

44:39.940 --> 44:40.860
[groans]

44:40.900 --> 44:44.380
You need help, Victor.

44:44.460 --> 44:46.980
You need medicine, water.

44:47.060 --> 44:48.060
We both need to eat.

44:48.100 --> 44:49.740
Quiet!

44:49.820 --> 44:51.660
Why'd you bring me here?

44:51.700 --> 44:52.700
Shut up.

44:55.060 --> 44:58.580
Victor, you came to me
for some reason.

44:58.660 --> 44:59.820
You're keeping me alive
for some reason.

44:59.860 --> 45:00.900
So you tell me what that is,

45:00.980 --> 45:01.860
we can do something
about it, yeah?

45:01.940 --> 45:02.860
Listen to me.

45:02.940 --> 45:04.020
You're Swedish, yeah?

45:04.060 --> 45:05.220
Yeah, yeah.

45:05.260 --> 45:07.740
There's snow?

45:07.820 --> 45:09.140
Where you come from,
there's snow, yeah?

45:09.220 --> 45:10.500
Yeah, and I can help you.

45:10.580 --> 45:11.860
I want to help you, all right?

45:11.900 --> 45:14.660
If you're going to help me,
I want to go there.

45:14.700 --> 45:17.340
What happened
to the white woman?

45:17.420 --> 45:18.940
If you tell me that,
I can help you.

45:19.020 --> 45:20.020
We can go.

45:21.540 --> 45:22.740
Bad spirits.

45:22.820 --> 45:24.460
Bad spirits took her.

45:26.260 --> 45:28.180
They lead her
to that place.

45:28.260 --> 45:29.900
Is she dead?

45:29.980 --> 45:31.420
I didn't touch her.

45:31.460 --> 45:32.660
I didn't kill her.

45:32.700 --> 45:34.580
She screamed--
she shouldn't have screamed.

45:34.660 --> 45:35.740
He was angry.

45:35.820 --> 45:37.060
Who was angry?

45:37.140 --> 45:39.300
Was that the man
who tried to shoot you,

45:39.380 --> 45:40.660
the man who cut your hand?

45:40.700 --> 45:42.260
I don't know why I tried
to help your friend.

45:42.340 --> 45:43.260
But you did?

45:43.340 --> 45:44.540
You tried to help her?

45:44.620 --> 45:45.660
He took her away.

45:45.740 --> 45:46.660
Where'd he take her?

45:46.740 --> 45:48.900
Victor, is this even safe?

45:48.980 --> 45:51.420
Does this man know
where you might have gone?

46:02.700 --> 46:03.700
[flies buzzing]

46:17.060 --> 46:19.060
My mama was killed
by witchcraft.

46:22.540 --> 46:23.860
My uncle took me to the city.

46:28.540 --> 46:29.460
To his friends...

46:29.540 --> 46:30.740
So I could have a second chance.

46:49.700 --> 46:51.260
Victor, who was this man?

46:51.300 --> 46:53.020
Can you tell me
who this man was?

46:53.060 --> 46:55.740
Where did he
take my friend?

46:58.380 --> 47:04.060
[speaking Xhosa language]

47:11.100 --> 47:11.980
Victor, we need...

47:12.060 --> 47:14.620
[shouting in Xhosa]

47:14.660 --> 47:16.460
Okay, okay, okay...

47:54.260 --> 47:55.820
If you got to...

48:03.900 --> 48:12.420
If I sorted it so that you could
come to Sweden with me,

48:12.460 --> 48:15.620
you'd see plenty of snow.

48:27.060 --> 48:29.060
Sweden's a good place.

48:35.060 --> 48:38.540
We try and help people
who've been hurt.

48:40.220 --> 48:42.140
You can't help me.

48:42.220 --> 48:43.700
You won't help me.

48:43.780 --> 48:46.500
What's this for, then?!

48:46.580 --> 48:48.460
I'm going to help you,
I said I'm going to help you.

48:48.500 --> 48:50.060
That's all I've said.

48:50.100 --> 48:52.380
I can't help you if you don't
tell me what I need to know!

48:52.460 --> 48:53.460
Why you were there?

49:02.660 --> 49:05.260
I was training.

49:05.300 --> 49:06.660
He was training me.

49:06.700 --> 49:08.980
Training?

49:09.060 --> 49:10.940
Training for what?

49:11.020 --> 49:13.860
To shoot?

49:13.940 --> 49:15.140
To shoot who?

49:18.020 --> 49:19.660
The black man.

49:23.780 --> 49:27.460
100,000 rand.

49:27.500 --> 49:31.660
That's how much the lives
of important people are.

49:40.620 --> 49:41.940
Who?

49:42.020 --> 49:45.420
Victor, who were you
trying to shoot?

49:52.020 --> 49:53.300
Call the police.

49:55.540 --> 50:00.020
I'll tell them that
I'll do it.

50:00.060 --> 50:02.660
[faint banging]

50:02.700 --> 50:04.220
Tell them that
we have a deal.

50:11.780 --> 50:13.780
[faint banging]

50:22.140 --> 50:24.140
VICTOR:
Go to Sweden.

50:24.220 --> 50:28.060
I'm coming to Sweden with you.

51:12.420 --> 51:13.660
WOMAN: <i>
Hello, how can I assist you?</i>

51:13.700 --> 51:15.340
Yeah.

51:15.420 --> 51:18.260
Yeah, my name is Kurt Wallander.

51:18.340 --> 51:22.020
I need to speak urgently
to Sergeant Grace Mthembu.

51:22.060 --> 51:23.740
WOMAN: <i>
Sergeant Mthembu?</i>

51:23.820 --> 51:26.500
<i>Just bear with me one moment,I'll see if she's at her desk.</i>

51:26.580 --> 51:30.380
[engine revving loudly]

51:34.980 --> 51:36.260
Come on, out of the car.

51:36.340 --> 51:37.300
Out of the car, come on, please!

51:37.380 --> 51:39.780
Come on, come on, come on!

51:39.860 --> 51:41.700
Come on, out of the car!

51:41.780 --> 51:43.300
Come on, come on,
out of the car!

51:43.380 --> 51:44.380
Out of the car!

52:29.260 --> 52:30.900
[engine revving]

52:45.140 --> 52:46.140
[coughing]

52:50.860 --> 52:52.380
[gasping]:
Friday...

52:56.060 --> 52:58.140
Friday...

52:58.220 --> 53:00.020
It's okay.

53:00.060 --> 53:01.500
It's okay.

53:01.580 --> 53:02.580
Friday...

53:39.340 --> 53:41.860
[flies buzzing]

53:58.940 --> 54:01.940
There's never a dull moment
with you, is there, Kurt?

54:10.660 --> 54:12.900
The bike is registered
to a man called Meyer.

54:12.980 --> 54:13.900
Ex-army.

54:13.980 --> 54:14.980
Mercenary.

54:35.940 --> 54:42.260
WALLANDER:
Victor said he was training
to shoot someone at the farm.

54:42.340 --> 54:47.820
A black man, someone important.

54:51.140 --> 54:52.340
"Friday."

54:52.420 --> 54:54.580
Hm?

54:54.660 --> 54:59.620
It was the last thing he said.

54:59.660 --> 55:03.620
"Friday."

55:03.660 --> 55:05.780
It has to be the day
of the shooting, doesn't it?

55:05.860 --> 55:08.780
Friday?

55:08.860 --> 55:11.900
Yeah, there's a big
election rally on that day.

55:11.980 --> 55:13.420
At Five Sisters.

55:15.540 --> 55:16.460
Bernie Meyiwa.

55:16.540 --> 55:17.540
Yeah.

55:18.860 --> 55:19.820
[dialing]

55:19.860 --> 55:21.140
<i>[phone ringing]</i>

55:21.220 --> 55:22.980
WOMAN: <i>
Hello?</i>

55:23.060 --> 55:26.540
GRACE:
Yeah, I need to speak
to Van Heerden, now.

55:26.620 --> 55:31.620
If this man wanted me dead,
why train up a boy like that?

55:31.660 --> 55:32.980
Why not do it himself?

55:33.060 --> 55:34.380
GRACE:
With all respect, sir,

55:34.460 --> 55:36.860
a white man kills you,
it's a tragedy.

55:36.940 --> 55:38.660
A black man
kills you...

55:38.700 --> 55:39.900
It's political.

55:39.980 --> 55:42.700
People will blame the ANC.

55:42.780 --> 55:44.660
30 years ago,

55:44.700 --> 55:46.380
would you have
listened to this?

55:46.460 --> 55:49.460
30 years ago,
I was in prison.

55:52.260 --> 55:53.860
It's the same
fight, Max.

55:53.940 --> 55:56.900
If I don't go up on that stage,
they'll say I'm a coward.

55:56.980 --> 55:59.220
And they'll be right.

55:59.260 --> 56:01.700
They need to see that
I can face these battles.

56:01.780 --> 56:03.100
And I can win.

56:03.180 --> 56:05.060
If you're dead,
you're no use to anyone.

56:06.420 --> 56:10.820
I will not be silenced
by a white man with a gun.

56:10.860 --> 56:16.820
You will catch this man,
and I will speak.

56:16.860 --> 56:19.620
And I will win.

56:22.380 --> 56:24.420
Okay, yeah, thank you.

56:24.460 --> 56:26.060
They've found
Meyer's flat.

56:35.060 --> 56:36.940
♪ ♪

56:49.700 --> 56:50.700
Sergeant.

57:21.540 --> 57:22.540
He was a security guard,
part-time.

57:22.620 --> 57:24.020
Western Cape Homes.

57:24.060 --> 57:26.100
He's been working there
since October 2013.

57:26.180 --> 57:27.660
GRACE:
Get over there.

57:27.740 --> 57:29.220
Take a unit.

57:32.100 --> 57:33.300
This is the company

57:33.380 --> 57:34.660
that's involved in one
of the developments

57:34.700 --> 57:36.780
that Bernie Meyiwa
is trying to stop.

57:36.860 --> 57:38.540
So do we need to...

57:38.620 --> 57:41.620
The security detail on the Five
Sisters rally's been told.

57:43.700 --> 57:47.500
Kurt, get some rest.

57:47.580 --> 57:48.980
I'll call you.

57:51.660 --> 57:53.060
Hm?

57:53.100 --> 57:54.500
Your keys.

58:08.980 --> 58:11.460
[waves crashing]

58:50.420 --> 58:53.060
Our role as a police force
is simple:

58:53.100 --> 58:55.300
maintain social order
by fighting crime.

58:55.380 --> 58:57.820
[talking echoes]

58:57.860 --> 59:02.380
[waves crashing, birds calling]

59:02.460 --> 59:04.460
[talking echoes more]

01:00:55.180 --> 01:00:57.180
[beeping]

01:01:02.660 --> 01:01:04.660
[dialing number]

01:01:04.740 --> 01:01:06.060
<i>[phone rings]</i>

01:01:06.100 --> 01:01:07.020
<i>Hello?</i>

01:01:07.060 --> 01:01:08.300
Grace, it's Kurt.

01:01:08.380 --> 01:01:09.700
I found Meyer's car.

01:01:09.780 --> 01:01:11.260
It's near his flat.

01:01:11.300 --> 01:01:13.060
And I've got his sat nav.

01:01:13.140 --> 01:01:16.660
He's been making repeated trips
to somewhere called Pinelands.

01:01:16.740 --> 01:01:18.140
It's near Forest Drive.

01:01:18.220 --> 01:01:20.580
That's Department
of Defense land.

01:01:20.660 --> 01:01:22.100
It's a disused military base.

01:01:22.180 --> 01:01:23.860
Could be where he took Inga--
I'll see you there.

01:01:23.900 --> 01:01:25.500
Wait, Kurt, why don't...?

01:01:25.580 --> 01:01:26.860
[sighs]

01:01:55.660 --> 01:01:57.900
[footsteps echoing]

01:02:10.900 --> 01:02:12.740
[flies buzzing]

01:02:21.980 --> 01:02:27.020
[flies buzzing]

01:03:18.500 --> 01:03:20.460
♪ ♪

01:04:02.820 --> 01:04:03.820
[grunts]

01:04:38.700 --> 01:04:39.860
[engine revving]

01:04:47.820 --> 01:04:48.820
[engine revving]

01:04:56.060 --> 01:04:57.260
[engine stops]

01:05:13.460 --> 01:05:15.260
[gun clicks]

01:05:32.180 --> 01:05:33.380
GRACE:
Kurt?!

01:05:34.180 --> 01:05:35.660
[screaming]

01:05:35.700 --> 01:05:38.460
[loud thud]

01:05:38.500 --> 01:05:40.220
GRACE:
Wallander?!

01:05:46.220 --> 01:05:49.660
Kurt?!

01:06:08.860 --> 01:06:12.860
Inga Hedeman's body's back there
in one of the water tanks.

01:06:12.940 --> 01:06:14.540
Are you okay?

01:06:24.580 --> 01:06:26.460
[dialing number]

01:06:26.540 --> 01:06:27.460
WOMAN: <i>Hello?</i>

01:06:27.500 --> 01:06:28.940
I need to speak
to Van Heerden.

01:06:29.020 --> 01:06:32.060
<i>Of course, please hold.</i>

01:06:32.140 --> 01:06:34.780
[vibrating]

01:06:45.020 --> 01:06:47.220
MAX: <i>
Meyer, what the hell
is going on?</i>

01:06:47.260 --> 01:06:50.540
<i>[peacocks calling]</i>

01:06:50.620 --> 01:06:52.060
<i>[call ends]</i>

01:06:56.660 --> 01:06:58.660
What is it?

01:07:01.940 --> 01:07:03.540
Khulu.

01:07:06.300 --> 01:07:09.260
That doesn't make any sense.

01:07:09.340 --> 01:07:10.540
It's him.

01:07:12.660 --> 01:07:15.100
I heard the peacocks
in the garden.

01:07:21.860 --> 01:07:22.780
Are you sure?

01:07:22.860 --> 01:07:24.260
I'm sure, Grace.

01:07:44.460 --> 01:07:46.140
[sighs]

01:07:50.300 --> 01:07:52.980
Okay, anything else you'd like
to add to the statement?

01:07:53.060 --> 01:07:54.300
No, that's it.

01:07:56.420 --> 01:07:58.460
Right.

01:08:00.860 --> 01:08:02.860
Here you go,
signature at the bottom.

01:08:17.660 --> 01:08:18.819
You okay?

01:08:18.859 --> 01:08:20.220
Yeah.

01:08:20.260 --> 01:08:21.380
I need to go through this.

01:08:22.660 --> 01:08:24.220
You need to get
some sleep.

01:08:24.260 --> 01:08:25.620
I'll call you
tomorrow.

01:08:25.660 --> 01:08:26.859
Yeah.

01:08:29.380 --> 01:08:30.540
You just take care, yeah?

01:08:30.620 --> 01:08:31.620
Yeah, yeah.

01:08:40.819 --> 01:08:44.180
♪ ♪

01:08:51.500 --> 01:08:53.939
Max Khulu set up a trust
owned by a holding company

01:08:54.020 --> 01:08:55.660
registered under his mother's
maiden name.

01:08:55.700 --> 01:08:59.260
It holds a 75% stake
in Western Cape Homes,

01:08:59.300 --> 01:09:02.700
and has done since
just before the company bid

01:09:02.779 --> 01:09:04.300
for a new luxury
housing development

01:09:04.380 --> 01:09:06.859
out in Sir Lowry's Pass.

01:09:06.899 --> 01:09:09.939
The trust also owns the land
being developed.

01:09:10.020 --> 01:09:14.500
Borrowed millions of rand
just to buy it up.

01:09:14.580 --> 01:09:17.260
He's put absolutely
everything into this.

01:09:18.859 --> 01:09:23.260
Past evidence says that
it'll quadruple in value,

01:09:23.300 --> 01:09:26.460
making Max Khulu
a very rich man.

01:09:26.500 --> 01:09:29.620
Unless, of course,
Bernie Meyiwa's elected

01:09:29.660 --> 01:09:33.140
and puts all these
developments on hold.

01:09:33.220 --> 01:09:37.460
So, 100,000 rand
doesn't seem like very much

01:09:37.540 --> 01:09:40.700
to invest in having
Bernie Meyiwa killed.

01:09:45.020 --> 01:09:46.660
I used to...

01:09:49.660 --> 01:09:53.060
My mother...

01:09:53.140 --> 01:09:54.900
She died of HIV.

01:09:54.980 --> 01:09:58.300
Max Khulu came
to open the clinic

01:09:58.380 --> 01:10:00.380
where my mother was.

01:10:04.180 --> 01:10:07.020
I just thought
he was different.

01:10:22.060 --> 01:10:25.180
[peacocks calling]

01:10:32.660 --> 01:10:34.020
We'd like to talk
to your husband.

01:10:34.060 --> 01:10:35.220
About what?

01:10:35.260 --> 01:10:37.060
What's the matter?

01:10:37.100 --> 01:10:42.540
I wasn't expecting to see you
again, Mr. Wallander.

01:10:42.620 --> 01:10:45.660
We just want to talk to you
about one or two things, sir.

01:10:48.180 --> 01:10:50.220
I have to go to the rally.

01:10:50.260 --> 01:10:51.780
Perhaps tomorrow.

01:10:51.860 --> 01:10:53.820
Your trust owns a stake
in Western Cape Home,

01:10:53.860 --> 01:10:55.340
is that correct?

01:10:55.420 --> 01:10:56.820
Through a holding company

01:10:56.860 --> 01:10:58.540
registered
in your mother's name.

01:11:00.860 --> 01:11:04.460
I believe they're part
of the trust's portfolio.

01:11:04.500 --> 01:11:06.260
Western Cape?

01:11:06.340 --> 01:11:09.700
A few shares, I think.

01:11:09.780 --> 01:11:11.580
To me, it seems
as though the trust

01:11:11.660 --> 01:11:12.900
is the majority
shareholder.

01:11:12.980 --> 01:11:16.060
No, I don't believe so.

01:11:16.140 --> 01:11:17.580
Your information is wrong.

01:11:17.660 --> 01:11:19.860
Were you aware that the man
who trained Victor Mabasha

01:11:19.940 --> 01:11:24.220
also works for Western Cape
as a security guard?

01:11:26.660 --> 01:11:28.340
Tell Colonel Van Heerden

01:11:28.420 --> 01:11:30.060
that I will see him
at the station

01:11:30.100 --> 01:11:31.620
at his convenience

01:11:31.660 --> 01:11:34.140
and answer
any further questions.

01:11:34.220 --> 01:11:35.660
But right now...

01:11:35.700 --> 01:11:37.140
May we see your phone?

01:11:53.420 --> 01:11:58.300
That's not the one you used,
is it?

01:11:58.380 --> 01:12:02.300
It's not the one you used
to call Meyer.

01:12:02.380 --> 01:12:04.540
I don't know anyone
by that name.

01:12:04.620 --> 01:12:06.580
You should know he's dead.

01:12:08.660 --> 01:12:13.380
He's dead, and Bernie Meyiwa's
going to stop that development.

01:12:19.060 --> 01:12:21.260
Was there
anything else?

01:12:24.860 --> 01:12:29.860
Bernie Meyiwa stands for
everything you fought for, sir.

01:12:29.900 --> 01:12:33.420
That's why I will stand
beside him today

01:12:33.460 --> 01:12:35.740
and make sure that he wins.

01:12:37.860 --> 01:12:39.580
The car's ready,
darling.

01:12:43.460 --> 01:12:45.020
The maid will
see you out.

01:12:50.780 --> 01:12:53.020
How many million rand
has he got invested in this?

01:12:53.060 --> 01:12:54.180
A couple of hundred.

01:12:54.260 --> 01:12:55.340
When's Bernie Meyiwa
scheduled to speak?

01:12:55.420 --> 01:12:56.340
20 minutes.

01:12:56.420 --> 01:12:57.460
Why is he
so calm?

01:13:01.460 --> 01:13:03.460
[birds calling]

01:13:09.220 --> 01:13:10.700
Hi.

01:13:13.980 --> 01:13:17.380
CROWD [chanting]:
Khulu!

01:13:17.460 --> 01:13:18.900
MAX:
Thank you.

01:13:18.980 --> 01:13:20.300
Thank you.

01:13:20.380 --> 01:13:23.740
Thank you, my people.

01:13:23.820 --> 01:13:26.860
Thank you.

01:13:26.900 --> 01:13:30.180
Thank you, my friends.

01:13:30.260 --> 01:13:34.260
Today is a day for my friend.

01:13:34.340 --> 01:13:35.580
My hope.

01:13:35.660 --> 01:13:37.740
Our hope.

01:13:37.820 --> 01:13:41.380
Comrade Bernie Meyiwa.

01:13:41.460 --> 01:13:48.100
[cheering]

01:13:48.180 --> 01:13:51.180
CROWD [chanting]:
Bernie!

01:13:56.340 --> 01:13:57.780
Grace!

01:13:57.860 --> 01:14:00.460
Why did Meyer need
a second training ground?

01:14:00.500 --> 01:14:02.620
Practice?

01:14:02.660 --> 01:14:04.220
But he's a professional--
why have two?

01:14:07.060 --> 01:14:09.260
Maybe he was training
another kid?

01:14:09.340 --> 01:14:10.460
He would have needed
a backup.

01:14:10.540 --> 01:14:11.420
Exactly.

01:14:11.460 --> 01:14:12.460
Let's find him.

01:14:32.500 --> 01:14:34.780
Grace! Grace!

01:14:34.860 --> 01:14:36.660
Grace?

01:14:36.740 --> 01:14:37.420
Grace!

01:14:37.460 --> 01:14:38.860
BERNIE:
Thank you!

01:14:38.940 --> 01:14:42.060
My friends.

01:14:42.100 --> 01:14:44.860
Thank you for coming.

01:14:44.900 --> 01:14:48.740
[in the distance]:
What do I promise you?

01:14:48.820 --> 01:14:51.820
I will make sure that
you have a share

01:14:51.860 --> 01:14:54.100
in the wealth
of this country.

01:14:54.180 --> 01:15:00.860
They say that Bernie Meyiwa
is simplistic and idealistic.

01:15:00.940 --> 01:15:04.540
I say, "What the hell
is wrong with that?"

01:15:04.620 --> 01:15:05.140
Wait.

01:15:05.220 --> 01:15:07.060
Wait, wait, wait.

01:15:07.140 --> 01:15:08.140
Meyer's dead.

01:15:08.220 --> 01:15:09.180
There's no money.

01:15:11.300 --> 01:15:13.580
I know who you are.

01:15:13.660 --> 01:15:14.620
I know why you're here.

01:15:14.660 --> 01:15:15.620
There was another boy

01:15:15.660 --> 01:15:16.820
just like you.

01:15:16.860 --> 01:15:18.820
Maybe you knew him--
his name was Victor.

01:15:18.860 --> 01:15:20.100
Another boy with a gun.

01:15:20.180 --> 01:15:21.100
He's dead.

01:15:21.180 --> 01:15:22.100
He's dead now.

01:15:22.180 --> 01:15:23.340
You can live.

01:15:25.660 --> 01:15:28.540
Listen to that man.

01:15:28.620 --> 01:15:30.620
Listen to what he's saying.

01:15:30.660 --> 01:15:32.180
That's who you'll be killing.

01:15:32.260 --> 01:15:36.340
You'll be killing him
for nothing.

01:15:40.900 --> 01:15:44.420
...when we have been caged
and trapped for so long!

01:15:46.580 --> 01:15:51.340
We need to show
our young men and women

01:15:51.420 --> 01:15:54.380
that they can still hope.

01:15:54.460 --> 01:15:59.940
We owe them this hope!

01:16:00.020 --> 01:16:05.180
We will deliver that hope
to them together!

01:16:05.260 --> 01:16:06.620
Just walk away.

01:16:08.820 --> 01:16:09.820
Walk away.

01:16:12.420 --> 01:16:13.660
Walk away.

01:16:13.740 --> 01:16:16.620
iAfrica! iAfrica!

01:16:16.660 --> 01:16:19.980
CROWD [chanting]:
iAfrica!

01:16:20.060 --> 01:16:21.140
BERNIE:
Mayibuye!

01:16:21.220 --> 01:16:22.180
CROWD:
iAfrica!

01:16:22.260 --> 01:16:23.260
BERNIE:
Mayibuye!

01:16:23.340 --> 01:16:24.780
CROWD:
iAfrica!

01:16:24.860 --> 01:16:29.340
BERNIE:
I promise you that
there will be a change.

01:16:29.420 --> 01:16:34.460
And when we decide that it is
time for a change together,

01:16:34.540 --> 01:16:36.500
when we have made up our minds

01:16:36.580 --> 01:16:39.860
that we will stand
shoulder to shoulder...

01:16:39.940 --> 01:16:41.420
iAfrica!

01:16:41.460 --> 01:16:42.460
CROWD:
Mayibuye!

01:16:42.540 --> 01:16:44.060
iAfrica!

01:16:44.100 --> 01:16:45.020
CROWD:
Mayibuye!

01:16:45.060 --> 01:16:46.020
iAfrica!

01:16:46.060 --> 01:16:47.180
CROWD:
Mayibuye!

01:16:47.260 --> 01:16:48.260
Mayibuye!

01:16:48.300 --> 01:16:49.260
CROWD:
iAfrica!

01:16:49.300 --> 01:16:50.340
Mayibuye!

01:16:50.420 --> 01:16:51.940
CROWD:
iAfrica!

01:16:52.020 --> 01:16:54.460
BERNIE:
There is no force
in the wonderful land of ours--

01:16:54.540 --> 01:16:58.500
there is no force
in this world--

01:16:58.580 --> 01:17:00.620
that can stop us!

01:17:00.660 --> 01:17:02.580
Amandla!

01:17:02.660 --> 01:17:03.660
Kurt!

01:17:08.740 --> 01:17:09.500
The shooter?

01:17:09.580 --> 01:17:10.580
He's gone.

01:17:16.460 --> 01:17:17.900
So has Khulu.

01:17:28.860 --> 01:17:31.060
[cheering]

01:17:44.140 --> 01:17:45.420
[gunshot]

01:18:13.060 --> 01:18:14.660
♪ ♪

01:18:37.020 --> 01:18:39.940
[grunting]

01:19:28.580 --> 01:19:30.580
[waves crashing]

01:19:56.340 --> 01:20:01.940
[applause]

01:20:02.020 --> 01:20:04.900
Do we make a difference?

01:20:04.980 --> 01:20:08.180
Maybe.

01:20:08.260 --> 01:20:11.260
Sometimes.

01:20:11.300 --> 01:20:15.500
Not much.

01:20:15.580 --> 01:20:22.460
What I do know is that
we should never stop trying.

01:20:22.500 --> 01:20:27.460
We need to remember that
every little counts.

01:20:30.180 --> 01:20:33.780
Recently, I met a young man
called Victor Mabasha.

01:20:33.860 --> 01:20:36.620
He was just a boy, really.
